# Anadigm / AnadigmDesigner2 lookups

Before answering any question about Anadigm chips (AN231E04, AN221E04,
AN220/AN120 families, etc.), AnadigmDesigner2 CAMs, I/O cells, clocks,
or auxiliary functions, **consult the local knowledge base first**.

## Where the info lives

- `docs/AN231E04.md` and `docs/phase-*.md` — project-specific notes.
- `~/dev/kbee-kb/cam-docs/` (outside the repo) — the full AD2 CAM
  documentation, converted from the `.chm` files under
  `~/.wine/.../AnadigmDesigner2/Program/ADDATA/`. Structure:
  - `README.md` — grouped index by family (`ANx3`, `ANx20`, `ANx21`,
    `ANx22`, `ANx27`, `AN12x`, `AN22x`).
  - `all.md` — single-file concatenation of every CAM doc (~180 KB);
    good for a broad Grep or a one-shot read when unsure which CAM is
    relevant.
  - `<CAM>/index.md` — per-CAM Markdown.
  - `<CAM>/index.html` + `<CAM>/assets/*.gif` — HTML with inline
    figures referenced by the Markdown.
  - `<CAM>/meta.json` — title + sha256 of the source `.chm`.

## How to search

1. For a question about a specific CAM type, `Grep` across
   `~/dev/kbee-kb/cam-docs/` for the keyword, or `Read` the matching
   `<CAM>/index.md` directly.
2. For "which CAM does X?" questions where you don't know the CAM
   name, `Grep` `all.md` first, then follow up on the specific
   `<CAM>/index.md` for full context.
3. Use `~/dev/kbee-kb/cam-docs/README.md` as the family-grouped index.

Do not fall back to web search or general training knowledge for
Anadigm CAM specifics while the local KB has the answer — it's
authoritative (extracted from the shipped AD2 help) and version-pinned.

## If files look stale or missing

Regenerate with `./scripts/convert-cam-docs.sh` from the repo root.
Output path can be overridden with `$KBEE_KB_DIR`.
